From 33a29bd7b05d6dbe96552a7341241005c80a0209 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: "Claude (HYDRA cleanup)" <claude@hydra.local>
Date: Mon, 27 Apr 2026 04:05:04 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] cleanup: rebrand to HYDRA V3, archive v1/v2 modules

- Move ChartMind/, ChartMindV2/, MarketMind/, NewsMind/ (root), GateMind/,
  SmartNoteBook/, LLMCore/, OandaAdapter/ to archive/
- Move Engine.py, main.py, position_monitor.py to archive/
- Move NewsMind/config/*.yaml to config/news/
- Add archive/README.md documenting what each archived item was for
- Update Dockerfile CMD to use engine/v3/main_v3.py (not legacy main.py)
- Add main_v3.py shim at project root for portable launching

V3 brain modules (chartmind/v3, marketmind/v3, newsmind/v2, gatemind/v3,
smartnotebook/v3, engine/v3, llm/) all import cleanly after the move.

This eliminates the case-sensitivity collision (ChartMind vs chartmind etc.)
that was causing checkout warnings on Windows.
